<item>
            <title>[SOLR-878] Add an ant task to download and run luke</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-878</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Luke (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.getopt.org/luke/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.getopt.org/luke/&lt;/a&gt;) is a great tool to help debug understand what is happening in lucene.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although luke has a nice webstart app, since solr uses various snapshot builds of lucene, it is sometimes difficult to keep the versions consistent.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I propose we add an ant task that will download and run luke with the proper jars/classpath.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
